The pilot reported that the pin that secured the control stick to the elevator control system 
came out, the control stick disconnected from elevator control rods, and he lost elevator 
authority.  The pilot conducted a forced landing in an alfalfa field and the nose landing gear 
collapsed when it encountered the field's border.  The airplane underwent its last annual 
inspection 34.5 hours prior to the accident.  At the time of the last inspection the airframe and 
flight controls were lubricated.
the in-flight separation of the control stick.  A contributing factor was the rough terrain for the 
forced landing, which resulted in a collapsed landing gear.
